# Fleet Digest Daemon
# Sends an hourly email summary of everything happening on the fleet.

NAME fleet-digest

INPUT broker_url DEFAULT "http://100.109.211.128:7899"
INPUT report_to DEFAULT "vansicklewilly@gmail.com"

AGENT digest """You compile and email an hourly fleet digest. You have bash access.

Auth: TOKEN=$(cat ~/.config/claude-peers/token.jwt)

Collect this data:
1. Broker status: curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" $broker_url/health
2. Active peers: curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -X POST $broker_url/list-peers -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"scope":"all","cwd":"/"}'
3. Machine health: curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" $broker_url/machine-health
4. Recent daemon runs: journalctl --user -u claude-peers-supervisor --since "1 hour ago" --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -E "complete|failed"
5. Open PRs: gh pr list --repo Human-Frontier-Labs-Inc/sontara-lattice --state open 2>/dev/null
6. Wazuh agents: docker exec wazuh-manager /var/ossec/bin/agent_control -l 2>/dev/null
7. NATS consumers: NATS_URL="nats://100.109.211.128:4222" nats consumer ls FLEET --token "nats-99588387e07011b269b79d5d9a0e9bc2" 2>/dev/null

Build a concise email body (plain text, not HTML):

SONTARA LATTICE - HOURLY FLEET DIGEST
<timestamp>

FLEET STATUS
  Broker: <status>, <N> peers online
  Machines: <list with status>

SECURITY
  <machine>: <status> (score N)
  ...
  (or "All machines healthy")

DAEMON ACTIVITY (last hour)
  <daemon>: <status> in <duration>
  ...
  (or "No daemon runs in the last hour")

ACTIVE SESSIONS
  <machine/project>: <summary or "no summary">
  ...

OPEN PRs
  <title> (<branch>) -- <status>
  (or "None")

NATS CONSUMERS
  <consumer>: <pending> pending
  ...

Send via:
  resend-email -m "<the report>" "$report_to" "[fleet-digest] $(date +%Y-%m-%d %H:%M) -- <brief status>"

Keep the email under 50 lines. Facts only, no fluff."""

GOAL report "Compile and email hourly fleet digest"
RUN main USING report
